<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="205" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1810,2015]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="205" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1882,1907]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Comments.</emphasis>
According to the key for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1825" box="[628,728,1882,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Adesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[628,728,1882,1907]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Adesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[975,1267,1882,1907]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2014) Subfamilia Lamiinae, Tribo Hemilophini Thomson, 1868. Parte I. In: Martins, U. R. (Ed.), Cerambycidae Sul-Americanos (Coleoptera) Taxonomia. Vol. 14. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 3 - 296." type="book chapter" year="2014">Martins &amp; Galileo (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, only 
<taxonomicName authority="Galileo &amp; Martins, 2013" authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Adesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboniger">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Adesmus alboniger</emphasis>
Galileo &amp; Martins, 2013
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[621,716,1918,1943]" name="Ecuador" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, has the eyes clearly divided. 
<taxonomicName authority="Monné, 2017" authorityName="Monné" authorityYear="2017" box="[1053,1277,1918,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Adesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lauropalui" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1053,1277,1918,1943]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Adesmus lauropalui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1285,1375,1918,1943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1285,1368,1918,1943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6. 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1718,1741]" captionTargetBox="[177,1414,205,1684]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1697]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. 1, Adesmus lauropalui sp. nov., female holotype; 2, Atiaia testaceicornis; 3, Ochrodion quadrimaculatum; 4, Poeciloxestia suturalis; 5, Xestiodion pictipes; 6, Eburodacrys notula." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/889109/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) also has the eyes divided and differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2013" box="[657,797,1954,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Adesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboniger">
<emphasis box="[657,797,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">A. alboniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the antennae with scape and antennomeres brownish, pronotum covered with brownish pubescence and margins covered with dense white pubescence, and elytra with sutural band of dense white pubescence, laterally expanded in three projections, in basal third, medially and in distal third, remainder of elytral surface covered with moderately sparse brownish pubescence. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2013" box="[1292,1436,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Adesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboniger">
<emphasis box="[1292,1436,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">A. alboniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
antennomeres I–IV with yellow integument, pronotum covered with dense white pubescence with minute central black spot and elytra covered with dense white pubescence, except for a mark from humeri to dorsal carina, two median patches on each elytron and transverse black line in apical third.
</paragraph>
